data.title: Real Housewives Of Atlanta star Drew Sidora mourns death of father Robert from Alzheimer's: 'I was a Daddy's Girl'
data.meta_description: 'You're never prepared for the inevitable, but here we are. It is with tears flowing, I announce that my father Dr. Robert A. Jordan has made his transition into Heaven,' wrote Drew.
data.text:
Real Housewives Of Atlanta star Drew Sidora emotionally announced Tuesday that her father Dr. Robert A. Jordan has died.

Robert suffered a heartbreaking decline as he struggled with Alzheimer's disease, occasionally failing to recognize his daughter.

The 38-year-old reality star posted an Instagram message breaking the news of his death, accompanied by a throwback slideshow remembering him.

In a moving touch, she set the slideshow to the Luther Vandross song Dance With My Father, in which he sang about how 'I knew for sure I was loved.'

'Youre never prepared for the inevitable, but here we are. It is with tears flowing, I announce that my father Dr. Robert A. Jordan has made his transition into Heaven,' wrote Drew. 'As my mom says, He fought a good fight and finished his race, with a smile on his face he picked up his crown at Heavens Gate!'

She warmly told her fans: 'Thank yall for allowing me to share my journey with my dad battling Alzheimers Disease. Thank you to all of you constantly messaging and writing me, sharing your own personal experiences with a loved one battling Alzheimers Disease and Dementia. Were forever connected!!'

Drew recalled: 'I was a Daddys Girl and I will cherish the precious memories that will forever live in my heart and his legacy lives forever! He was the best pediatrician in all of Chicago and if you knew, you knew! He was passionate about helping people, saving lives and providing quality healthcare to those in the indigent community.'

She proudly noted: 'He served 4 generations or patients within his practice and he will truly be missed. He had the most humble and sweetest spirit and we will celebrate HIS LIFE!!!!! Thank you for your condolences and please keep my family in your prayers as we grieve I thank God, knowing we will see you Daddy again!'

On an episode of The Real Housewives Of Atlanta earlier this year, Drew revealed she had a 'breakdown' when she visited her father in his Chicago nursing home.

However her spirits improved when her mother Rev. Jeannette B. Jordan appeared on the scene, whereupon Robert started to remember Drew more clearly.

Drew, who is a singer alongside her career as a reality star, revealed on the Bravo show that she also played her father her new song in the nursing home.

'My dad does not recognize me all the time, but when he heard me singing and knew that it was me, I was extremely emotional, because that has been our connection my whole life,' Drew revealed on camera afterwards.

She told her husband Ralph Pittman: 'I think Ive been pretty strong through it, but literally, when I go back to Chicago, its like: "Oh, wow, Daddys in a nursing home."'

During her visit to the nursing home, she saw that her father was wheelchair-bound, which astonished her 'because when he went in, he was still walking.'

Drew's year has been wracked with emotional turmoil, including not only her father's decline and death but also the dramatic collapse of her marriage to Ralph.

Days after Drew threw Ralph an opulent 40th birthday party, the pair separated, bringing the curtain down on nine years of marriage.

'For three years, the Pittmans' welcomed millions of viewers into their home as they struggled to repair their marriage,' Drew's spokesman told DailyMail.com.

'Despite undeniable differences, they agree that their marriage is irretrievably broken and are going their separate ways.'
